    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="866"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d866">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.711/1</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-19">
                        <hi rend="italic">September 19, 1914</hi>.</date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received October 5</hi>.] </dateline>
                <p rend="flushleft">No. 467]</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to transmit herewith an inquiry,
                    with accompanying enclosures, received from the American Legation at The Hague,
                    with reference to the regulations and authorization under which the British
                    censor is opening mail of the American Consular Service.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PWH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Walter Hines Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <note rend="inline" rendition="#center">[Enclosure]</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName
                            corresp="#p_VDH1" type="from">
                            <hi rend="italic">Van Dyke</hi>
                        </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi>
                            (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to">
                            <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                        </persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Hague</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-04">
                                <hi rend="italic">September 4, 1914</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>The American Legation at The Hague requests information in regard to
                        regulations and authorization under which the British officials are opening
                        mail of the American Consular Service, some of which, as is evident from the
                        enclosed envelopes,<note n="2" xml:id="d866fn1">Not printed.</note> is under
                        official seal.</p>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
